author: Daniel Kilkelly
title: UK TV ratings: EastEnders brings in 6.4m with Les Coker shock - EastEnders Soaps -
text: UK TV soap ratings roundup - data supplied by BARBEastEnders topped the ratings on Thursday (October 15) with Donna Yates's shocking discovery, overnight figures show.6.42m (33.2%) tuned in at 7.30pm on BBC One as Donna was stunned to find Les in Claudette's living room wearing only his underpants. BBC Three's repeat added 309k (1.9%) at 10pm. © BBC / Nicky JohnstonRoger Sloman as Les Coker Emmerdale rose to 6.06m (32.7%) at 7pm on ITV and 102k (0.5%) on +1 as Aaron's gun secret was exposed, while 5.78m (28.6%) returned at 8pm and 198k (0.9%) on +1 to see the troubled character get arrested.Hollyoaks attracted 809k (4.7%) at 6.30pm on Channel 4 as Trevor tried to make a deal with Ashley (+1: 69k / 0.4%), while E4's first look followed with 653k (3.5%) at 7pm and 134k (0.7%) on +1.Doctors interested 1.37m (22.1%) at 1.45pm on BBC One as Emma went for her first baby scan with Howard. © BBCDido Miles as Emma Reid Neighbours claimed 681k (10.9%) at 1.45pm and 675k (5.1%) at 5.30pm on Channel 5 with the fallout from Brad's big move.Home and Away managed 206k (3.4%) at 1.15pm and 546k (3.5%) at 6pm on Channel 5, while 5*'s first look had 345k (2.0%) at 6.30pm.
